Event is something is happened on your page.
you pressed a button its an event
you move your mouse its an event

now we will learn how to handle the event...

##event listenter
by using this you will handle the evennt

element.addEventListener("event", function)

in here first you will declare the event like is it click mouse over or etc.
than you deploy the function for what you wanna do...

example:

let btn = document.querySelector("button");                  // button selected by dom

btn.addEventListener("click", function() {                  //using the click event and using the arrow function for execution
    console.log("Button clicked!");
});

##some of common event:
"click" → user clicks
"mouseover" → mouse goes over
"mouseout" → mouse leaves

